data.description: Own a piece of history!  Nestled in the picturesque town of Kintersville this exceptional property boasts 12.2 acres of land.  Situated on the property is a beautiful Victorian house which holds 4 bedrooms, 2 full bath and half bath on the first floor as well as an inlaw suite.  The home is flooded with natural light due to the many windows. The house also has an office suite on the top floor.  This is truly old school charm meets 21st Century convenience. Also on the property are several other structures that were used in the past as a Blacksmith Shop, Antique Store, Lumber Mill, and a pole barn that collects a monthly income of $100 (month to month).  One can easily embrace the beauty of nature with the possibilities for gardening, outdoor recreation and breathtaking views in all seasons.  Create your own oasis within this peaceful landscape. After doing your due diligence an investor may find 2 buildable lots on the property which may present an excellent investment opportunity.   Don't miss out on this incredible opportunity to make this versatile property your own. Whether you're searching for a unique place to call home or an investment venture with potential, 9754 Easton Road, Kintnersville, has it all. Contact us today to explore the possibilities and make your real estate dreams a reality.
